          "text": "The Lebesgue Dominated Convergence Theorem",
          "subparts": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(b)",
          "text": "Fatou’s Lemma",
          "subparts": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(c)",
          "text": "The Radon–Nikodym Theorem",
          "subparts": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(d)",
          "text": "\\((L^1(S,\\Sigma,\\mu))^* = L^\\infty(S,\\Sigma,\\mu)\\)",
          "subparts": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "number": 2,
      "text": "State and prove the Vitali Convergence Theorem for integrals (convergence in measure form).",
      "subparts": []
    },
    {
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Show that a subset \\(A\\) of the reals is a set of Lebesgue measure zero if and only if there exists a sequence of intervals \\(I_m\\) such that",
      "subparts": [
        {
          "label": "(a)",
          "text": "\\(\\displaystyle \\sum_m \\operatorname{length}(I_m)<\\infty.\\)",
          "subparts": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(b)",
          "text": "\\(\\displaystyle A\\subset \\bigcup_{m=k}^{\\infty} I_m\\) for every \\(k\\).",
          "subparts": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Let \\(f\\) be Lebesgue integrable on \\(\\mathbb R\\). Suppose that \\(\\displaystyle \\int_0^x f\\,dm=0\\) for every \\(x\\in\\mathbb R\\). What can you conclude about \\(f\\)?",
      "subparts": []
    },
    {
      "number": 5,
      "text": "State and prove Fubini’s Theorem.",
      "subparts": []
    },
    {
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Let \\((S_m,\\Sigma_m,P_m)_{m=1}^{\\infty}\\) be a sequence of probability spaces. Let \\(E_m\\in\\Sigma_m\\), \\(m=1,2,\\ldots\\).",
      "subparts": [
        {
          "label": "(a)",
          "text": "Show that \\[E=\\mathop{\\times}_{m=1}^{\\infty}E_m\\in\\bigotimes_{m=1}^{\\infty}\\Sigma_m.\\]",
          "subparts": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(b)",
          "text": "Prove that \\[\\left(\\bigotimes_{m=1}^{\\infty}P_m\\right)(E)=\\prod_{m=1}^{\\infty}P_m(E_m).\\]",
          "subparts": []
        }
      ]
    }
